message.content:
DARKNESS had descended like a curtain by the
time they docked at Rellery. And though Guy,
made nervous by Beryl's silence, drove at reckless
speed to the villa, it was quickly evident that
the party was over. Pies came strolling out to
meet the Deaves, and as soon as Guy had
driven away, invited them casually to come to
his flat for a drink.
